Worker fell from leader: heavily injures
With the replacement of a defective external feeler a 51-year old worker fell into Eggelsberg of a leader and injured themselves heavily on Thursday.
The man from Lamprechtshausen wanted a defective heating feeler replacement at the external facade of a hotel.
When it rose to the ladder leaned against the gutter, this slipped away and the man fell on the concrete floors.
It suffered heavy injuries and with the emergency rescue helicopter “Christophorus 6” into the state hospital Salzburg was brought.
